<div data-markdown>
<script type="text/template">
## &lt;input&gt; tag

The input tag can take in textual input, passwords, or act as submit
button.

* type - button / *checkbox* / color / date / datetime /  datetime-local / email
/  file /  *hidden* /  image / month / number / password /  *radio* /
range / reset / search /  *submit* / tel /  *text* /  time / url / week
* name - the name of the data sent to the URI
* value - the default value
Hidden types allow you to embed values to send along to help the request.

</script>
</div>
</section>
<!-- ######################## END MARKDOWN SLIDE ########################## -->



