<script type="text/template">
## CGI Diversion

In the lab you setup a CGI server and wrote a very small CGI script.

Did you know you can write CGI in just about any language?

All it takes is printing HTTP Response headers, reading environment
variables and reading from STDIN!

Here's a minimal PERL example
````
#!/usr/bin/perl
use Data::Dumper;
print "Content-type: text/plain\r\n\r\n";
print Dumper(\%ENV);
my $line = 0;
while(<>) {
	print $line++ . " " . $_ . $/;
}
````
</script>
</div>
</section>
